  "texts": [
    "Its ability to handle complex data patterns and avoid overfitting enhances its utility in identifying and classifying suspicious transactions.",
    "Graph Convolutional Networks (GCNs) stand out for their effectiveness in analyzing graph-structured data, such as transaction networks in cryptocurrencies (Weber et al., 2018; Alarab and Prakoonwit, 2022b; Wei et al., 2023).",
    "GCNs can detect anomalous behaviour and illicit transactions that may evade traditional detection methods by modeling the relationships between nodes in a graph.",
    "Their ability to capture complex relationships within transaction networks makes them valuable tools for improving the accuracy and efficiency of AML efforts.",
    "The application of these models in real-world AML practices offers several benefits."
